                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.5914/33</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-16T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 16, 1915, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>173. In reference to your telegram of August 10, 11 a.m., number 37, regarding
                    question of Danish West Indies. It is evident that from the necessity of keeping
                    up the popular benevolent institutions and maintaining the <hi rend="italic"
                        >quasi</hi> mobilization the Danish Government will soon need money.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Egan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
